examples.en: A crowd of people awaited the train.
He awaited the signal to start.
They awaited news of the outcome.
She awaited her punishment with dread.
He awaited word from his man in Havana.
I oiled round to where Jeeves awaited me.
The captains of thousands awaited his commands.
His reappearance as Hamlet has been long awaited.
Europe, in breathless suspense, awaited the issue.
His new book is anxiously awaited by fans everywhere.
A terrible surprise awaited them at Mr Tumnus' house.
Her long-awaited new novel is finally being published.
The players anxiously awaited the verdict of the umpire.
Reporters awaited confirmation from the army about the battle.
Spencer's father had died young, and he feared that the same fate awaited him.
A great breadth of land awaited those who were brave and hardy enough to settle it.
The city was in ferment as its residents nervously awaited the airborne invasion that was sure to come.
A forthcoming exhibit at the art museum that is eagerly awaited by connoisseurs of ancient Greek pottery.
